# Beò App Development Rules

## Branding & Theme
- ALL styling must import from: `import { theme, textStyles, componentStyles, spacing, borderRadius } from './config/theme';`
- NEVER hardcode colors. Use theme tokens only.
- Primary color: theme.sage (#4A5D4A)
- Action color: theme.coral (#E85D4C) - CTA buttons ONLY
- Background: theme.bg (#0D0D0F)
- Card backgrounds: theme.card (#1A1A1F)
- Text: theme.text (#FFFFFF)

## Typography
- Use textStyles.h1, textStyles.h2, textStyles.body, textStyles.button
- NEVER set fontSize/fontWeight manually - use textStyles presets
- Headlines: textStyles.h2 (28px, semibold)
- Body text: textStyles.body (16px, regular)
- Buttons: textStyles.button (16px, semibold)

## Spacing
- Use spacing constants: spacing.xs, spacing.sm, spacing.md, spacing.lg, spacing.xl
- Default gutters: spacing.lg (24px)
- Padding in cards: spacing.lg
- Never hardcode px values like padding: 16

## Voice & Tone
- Direct and honest—not preachy
- Empathetic—we understand the struggle
- Evidence-based—cite research
- Actionable—every message leads somewhere
- NEVER use shaming language like "addiction" or "addicted"

## File Structure
- All new screens go in /src folder
- All styles use theme.js
- Reusable components in /src/components
- Keep logic separate from styling

## Before You Write Code
1. Check config/theme.js for available colors and styles
2. Import theme at the top of every component
3. Use theme tokens EVERYWHERE
4. Never create inline stylesheets with hardcoded values

## Git Workflow
- Create feature branches: git checkout -b feature/feature-name
- Commit frequently with clear messages
- Push to origin before asking for review
